# AI-Driven NLP Sentiment Analysis Project

 Project Overview
This project implements a Sentiment Analysis system using Python and Natural Language Processing (NLP).  
It analyzes user text and classifies it as Positive, Negative, or Neutral based on polarity scores.

Technologies Used
- Python
- TextBlob
- Matplotlib
- Google Colab

⚙️ How It Works
1. Takes text input from user.
2. Calculates sentiment polarity using TextBlob.
3. Classifies sentiment:
   - Positive (polarity > 0)
   - Negative (polarity < 0)
   - Neutral (polarity = 0)
4. Visualizes sentiment scores using bar graph.

📊 Features
- Single sentence analysis
- Multiple sentence analysis
- Sentiment polarity visualization
- Real-world NLP application

 Applications
- Social Media Monitoring
- Customer Feedback Analysis
- Review Classification
- Chatbot Sentiment Detection

Conclusion
This project demonstrates practical implementation of NLP and AI techniques for sentiment analysis.
